The paper deals with the problem of constructing a data structure to efficiently answer queries on a graph, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper focuses on the distance sensitivity oracle, which is a well-studied problem in the field of graph algorithms and data structures. The paper proposes an improved structure for the distance sensitivity oracle, which is based on tree partitioning. This technique is commonly used in the design of efficient algorithms and data structures for graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
